Name: Balm Lily Flower
Description:
A medicinal flower that soothes most minor maladies.

It is exceptionally fragrant.

Name: Reed Fiber
Description: A ball of raw cellulose used in the production of Clothing and textiles.

Name: Gas Grass
Description: Gas grass.

Name: Lumber
Description: Wood harvested from an Arbor Tree or an Oakshell.

Name: Snazzy Suit
Description: Increases Decor in a small area effect around the wearer. Can be upgraded to Primo Garb at the Clothing Refashionator

Name: Primo Garb
Description: Increases Decor in a small area effect around the wearer

Name: Warm Sweater
Description: Protects the wearer from Cold by increasing insulation

Name: Cool Vest
Description: Protects the wearer from Heat by decreasing insulation

Name: Oxygen Mask
Description: Supplies Duplicants with Oxygen in toxic and low breathability environments.

Name: Worn Oxygen Mask
Description:
A worn out Oxygen Mask.

Masks can be repaired at a Crafting Station.

Name: Tonic Root
Description:
A chewy, fibrous rhizome with a fiery aftertaste.

It relieves gassiness.

Name: Data Bank
Description: Raw Data that can be processed into Data Analysis Research points.

Name: Egg Shell
Description: Can be crushed to produce Lime.

Name: Small Pokeshell Molt
Description: Can be crushed to produce Lime.

Name: Pokeshell Molt
Description: Can be crushed to produce Lime.

Name: Small Oakshell Molt
Description: Can be crushed to produce Lumber.

Name: Oakshell Molt
Description: Can be crushed to produce Lumber.

Name: Table Salt
Description: A seasoning that Duplicants can add to their Food to boost Morale. Duplicants will automatically use Table Salt while sitting at a Mess Table during mealtime. Only the finest grains are chosen.

Name: Atmo Suit
Description: Supplies Duplicants with Oxygen in toxic and low breathability environments.

Name: Worn Atmo Suit
Description:
A worn out Atmo Suit.

Suits can be repaired at an Exosuit Forge.

Name: Jet Suit
Description:
Supplies Duplicants with Oxygen in toxic and low breathability environments.

Allows Duplicant flight.

Name: Worn Jet Suit
Description:
A worn out Jet Suit.

Suits can be repaired at an Exosuit Forge.

Name: Lead Suit
Description: Supplies Duplicants with Oxygen in toxic and low breathability environments.

Name: Worn Lead Suit
Description:
A worn out Lead Suit.

Suits can be repaired at an Exosuit Forge.

Name: Radbolts
Description: A concentrated field of Radbolts that can be largely redirected using a Radbolt Reflector.

Name: Vacillator Recharge
Description: Replenishes one charge to a depleted Neural Vacillator.

Name: Rot Pile
Description:
An inedible glop of former foodstuff.

Rot Piles break down into Polluted Dirt over time.
